    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-17T14:21:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-17T14:21:00-05:00" n="336"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/7–1654: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d336fn1">Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_POPPERDH1">Popper</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-17T15:21:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1954—3:21 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. For <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">Lodge</persName>. <gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 45. <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>
                    Presidency. As we are now committed to <persName corresp="#p_WWPWWKNB1">Prince
                        Wan</persName>, I believe any approach to <persName corresp="#p_KLEFFENSEN1"
                        >Van Kleffens</persName> based on the assumption latter might be elected
                        <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> President would only give Dutch cause to
                    charge us with bad faith when they learn of our commitment. I would not want to
                    do anything to add to our difficulties in explaining to the Dutch why we cannot
                    support <persName corresp="#p_KLEFFENSEN1">Van Kleffens</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
